comments.text: Hello world. This is Moroccoüá≤üá¶ not the glossy postcards you see, but the hidden truth. Families who lost everything in the 2023 earthquake are still living in tents, waiting for homes that never come. Hospitals are overcrowded and without medicine, mothers wait for hours only to be told there is nothing for their children. Schools are packed with too many students and too few teachers, leaving children with diplomas that mean nothing because there are no jobs. Entire neighborhoods are destroyed to build stadiums and luxury projects, while the poor are pushed out of their houses with nowhere to go. Young people who raise their voices are silenced, beaten, or jailed, their dreams crushed before they are born. Children are forced to work in the streets instead of learning in classrooms, some disappearing into places where no one asks questions. Poverty is everywhere ‚Äî fathers with empty hands, mothers crying because they cannot feed their families, youth staring at a future that does not exist. This is the Morocco that lives in silence, the Morocco the world does not see, the Morocco that deserves justice, dignity, and hope.
